column1: # Seasonal Adjustment: Seasonally Adjusted Annual Rate

Real gross domestic product is the inflation adjusted value of the goods and services produced by labor and property located in the United States.For more information see the Guide to the National Income and Product Accounts of the United States (NIPA). For more information
column2: please visit the Bureau of Economic Analysis (http://www.bea.gov/national/pdf/nipaguid.pdf).
